  "texts": [
    "These traditional factors are interpretable.",
    "Factors can also can be constructed directly from previous realized asset returns using methods such as principal component analysis (PCA) [BN08, Bai03, LP20a, LP20b, PX22b, PX22a].",
    "Aside from the first principal component, which typically is close to the market return, these factors are less interpretable.",
    "Factor and idiosyncratic returns.",
    "A factor model gives an alternative method to specify the expected return as µ = F f + ε, where f is a forecast of the factor returns and ε is a forecast of the idiosyncratic returns, i.e., the asset alphas."
